<body>
    <h1>Task 21 -Technical Document</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 local-id=3D"f55527caec06" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-1.Intr=
oduction">1. Introduction</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"04ef5ba681ff" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-1.1Purpose">1.=
1 Purpose</h3>
<p local-id=3D"8de87aad54be">This Technical Document provides a detailed ac=
count of the implementation of an Azure App Service deployment with a Hello=
 World application, custom domain mapping using CNAME and TXT DNS records, =
and DNS validation including SOA record inspection. The intended audience f=
or this document includes:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"8e64e00a68a9">
<li local-id=3D"4776d402e083">
<p local-id=3D"ac397f420406"><strong>CTO</strong> =E2=80=94 for strategic o=
versight and validation of the Azure-hosted application approach</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6a544ea9ff87">
<p local-id=3D"e91c5ead3181"><strong>Developers</strong> =E2=80=94 for unde=
rstanding the deployment process, custom domain configuration, and DNS reco=
rd setup</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2357ac3bd6e9">
<p local-id=3D"88fecd1fd443"><strong>Solution Architects</strong> =E2=80=94=
 for reviewing the Azure infrastructure design and DNS architecture decisio=
ns</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1c149f521640">
<p local-id=3D"8b85e691c0d5"><strong>DevOps Engineers</strong> =E2=80=94 fo=
r replicating, maintaining, or extending this setup</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"195e37947bc8">
<p local-id=3D"a2083b11a06f"><strong>Resellers</strong> =E2=80=94 for under=
standing the solution stack and deployment model for client engagements</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"dc9130826aaa" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-1.2Scope">1.2 =
Scope</h3>
<p local-id=3D"38ad2400bbbd">This document covers the end-to-end technical =
implementation of:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"3c2fe4638e7d">
<li local-id=3D"0e8b2e5bebb4">
<p local-id=3D"8854939b1e4e">Creating an Azure App Service (Web App) with P=
ython 3.14 runtime on Linux</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"af290ae4fb1c">
<p local-id=3D"556571abe8cc">Deploying a Hello World application accessible=
 via the default Azure domain</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3a84074cd7f6">
<p local-id=3D"e27a8536e7bf">Creating CNAME and TXT DNS records in AWS Rout=
e 53 for custom domain mapping</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ce8f2c0330e6">
<p local-id=3D"18a19101b28d">Mapping the custom domain <code>app.karna.push=
kar.cloud</code> to the Azure App Service</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"486279491ea5">
<p local-id=3D"905b9390bb92">Validating DNS resolution using <code>nslookup=
</code> from a local Windows machine</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a16f897204d0">
<p local-id=3D"1dbf16893e96">Inspecting and documenting the SOA record of t=
he DNS zone</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"e52500728f0a">This document does not cover CI/CD pipeline co=
nfiguration, production-grade scaling, multi-region deployment, or Azure De=
vOps pipeline integration.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"e67e292fc017">
<h2 local-id=3D"d0be722c2e91" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-2.OverviewofDe=
vOpsProject">2. Overview of DevOps Project</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"c45301aa5712" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-2.1Definition"=
>2.1 Definition</h3>
<p local-id=3D"bd4e99c00f60">DevOps is a set of practices, tools, and cultu=
ral philosophies that automate and integrate the processes between software=
 development and IT operations teams. The goal is to shorten the systems de=
velopment lifecycle and provide continuous delivery of high-quality softwar=
e.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c26546405b95">In this project, a core cloud hosting componen=
t of a DevOps workflow is established =E2=80=94 deploying a web application=
 on Azure App Service and exposing it through a custom domain backed by DNS=
 configuration in AWS Route 53. This demonstrates cross-cloud DNS managemen=
t and Azure PaaS application hosting capabilities.</p>
<p local-id=3D"77c7fc369299"><strong>Key benefits realized in this implemen=
tation:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"e6781aee65cb">
<li local-id=3D"437e3fafb143">
<p local-id=3D"ee49046992a4">Rapid application hosting using Azure's fully =
managed PaaS platform without managing underlying infrastructure</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"64c9d99b1f92">
<p local-id=3D"3f9c43f059e5">Custom domain mapping providing a branded, pro=
fessional URL for the application</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"be4a040da486">
<p local-id=3D"15df8d863fd8">Cross-cloud DNS management using AWS Route 53 =
to point to Azure App Service</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0d5a5054ba6f">
<p local-id=3D"947633a4f069">HTTPS-secured access via Microsoft's managed S=
SL certificate on the default Azure domain</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e3a6822b8332">
<p local-id=3D"fd47cd703bbb">DNS validation knowledge through TXT record ve=
rification and SOA record inspection</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"5be4854a71d9" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-2.2KeyPrincipl=
es=E2=80=94AWSWell-ArchitectedFramework(6Pillars)">2.2 Key Principles =E2=
=80=94 AWS Well-Architected Framework (6 Pillars)</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"5=
9dbb425-5174-4835-bbaa-24a70b8f5cf1" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"9ea874c4e3bb">
<th data-local-id=3D"b8dcf5940898" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"42999609c8ac">Pillar</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"f757c12b2b26" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"b3179ad5af47">How It Was Achieved</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"452d2b08e443">
<td data-local-id=3D"ddac41299f31" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"31f8878256be"><strong>Operational Excellence</strong></p></t=
d>
<td data-local-id=3D"e5782f364ca8" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d94f3b03bedd">Azure App Service provides managed infrastruct=
ure; deployment and domain configuration done through the Azure Portal with=
 a structured, repeatable process; DNS records created in AWS Route 53 with=
 clear naming conventions</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b9b0057186c2">
<td data-local-id=3D"f121a7a0f2c9" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2c13dacde334"><strong>Security</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ca5ad344a119" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1e8c031d5de7">HTTPS enforced via Microsoft-managed SSL certi=
ficate (<code>*.azurewebsites.net</code>); TXT record used for domain owner=
ship verification before custom domain was mapped; Azure subscription-level=
 access control applied</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"6f6b5d5a82f9">
<td data-local-id=3D"51bfde8674e8" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"394fa658269b"><strong>Reliability</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f3d4f4ee4133" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e16455a97a16">Azure App Service (P0v3 plan) provides built-i=
n high availability; the managed PaaS platform handles OS patching, load ba=
lancing, and auto-restart of the application</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2595c1f373ab">
<td data-local-id=3D"326ec5f9899a" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"57986ccd9a8b"><strong>Performance Efficiency</strong></p></t=
d>
<td data-local-id=3D"328128d7c234" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4ac4e645f210">App Service Plan P0v3 (Linux) right-sized for =
a Hello World PoC; Python 3.14 runtime used for minimal overhead; Azure Cen=
tral US region selected for appropriate latency</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"0719f9e74d33">
<td data-local-id=3D"dde2c8667473" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1088823f5ecb"><strong>Cost Optimization</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3782451ed3f7" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7e94bc43d409">Azure App Service PaaS model eliminates VM man=
agement overhead; P0v3 plan selected as the minimum viable tier; DNS manage=
d using existing AWS Route 53 hosted zone at no additional cost</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4e92a779d4d8">
<td data-local-id=3D"6a5912458679" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a19b03910457"><strong>Sustainability</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"52c7bc8cd581" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f3544fd99982">PaaS deployment reduces energy overhead compar=
ed to IaaS VMs; shared infrastructure model of App Service optimizes physic=
al resource utilization</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"6bd22bede751" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-2.3GoalsandObj=
ectives">2.3 Goals and Objectives</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"93bd74f8a5b6">
<li local-id=3D"3fdc1627a512">
<p local-id=3D"bc70c6f32ee3">Deploy a functional Hello World application on=
 Azure App Service accessible via the default Azure URL</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d6b736c7f50d">
<p local-id=3D"db8d43dd64d1">Configure a custom domain (<code>app.karna.pus=
hkar.cloud</code>) pointing to the Azure App Service</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"00e5869829e9">
<p local-id=3D"d19cb0cf6dbb">Create and validate CNAME and TXT DNS records =
in AWS Route 53</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4a8515e1d0ff">
<p local-id=3D"8dc2d754ba94">Verify DNS resolution using <code>nslookup</co=
de> commands from a local Windows machine</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bbd4f96911b4">
<p local-id=3D"04f84c7d00ec">Inspect and document all fields of the SOA rec=
ord of the <code>karna.pushkar.cloud</code> DNS zone</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"803d4d5b3c08">
<p local-id=3D"e80c7e9129c7">Document the complete process for knowledge tr=
ansfer and reproducibility</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"ed0518f4ba4b" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-2.4Constraints=
andAssumptions">2.4 Constraints and Assumptions</h3>
<p local-id=3D"d78535618424"><strong>Constraints:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d=
a228b1b-cc14-4348-a961-e66164cd8d8a" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"da8635f2b054">
<th data-local-id=3D"247c5707ad20" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"0b632178fc6e">Constraint</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"efc46650a84e" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"2d5cec979afd">Detail</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"58051fe71cc6">
<td data-local-id=3D"9dfb772dcf51" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e9c5dcc312a4">Time</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4939a4192af5" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9ce753a37361">Task must be completed within 3 hours</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d1839c4a1f9c">
<td data-local-id=3D"a27c4c2fa937" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d12b491c0f23">Budget</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8dff0c9a8517" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b89f501404a6">Azure lab account (azurekmlprod) with limited =
subscription scope</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"fb72fd0af1b6">
<td data-local-id=3D"78492ed500c3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"977f607307bd">Technology</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"705ad197dfa2" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9ad657d2aa22">Azure App Service (PaaS); no custom VM or cont=
ainer-based deployment</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"41701820ffb2">
<td data-local-id=3D"74fa9a1949c2" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"93d5b5b0da96">Runtime</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e61aae163680" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d3ba2365a149">Python 3.14 on Linux OS</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"db7fe8836516">
<td data-local-id=3D"a74a72e14e91" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"78c0dc1dd2e0">DNS Provider</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"582dd2bcb9f0" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6ee996f54ed1">AWS Route 53 (existing hosted zone for karna.p=
ushkar.cloud)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"6211a168f391">
<td data-local-id=3D"62b5e47e3f47" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8c1c3cc1de4e">Region</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7b3eed0db9fd" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c9f82aa9bf6b">Azure Central US</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3a59b6b3ea33">
<td data-local-id=3D"9ae931f23690" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b0e1683cec99">SSL</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e56a88cd98d9" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"381d16ce8eae">Microsoft-managed certificate for default doma=
in; custom domain accessed without custom SSL in this PoC</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"0fb1f38ee78f"><strong>Assumptions:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"bdb8f255fdb5">
<li local-id=3D"df1069b04ad5">
<p local-id=3D"aaf0d6192419">The Azure lab account has sufficient permissio=
ns to create App Service resources</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f84c35d45364">
<p local-id=3D"01994db83c99">The domain <code>karna.pushkar.cloud</code> is=
 already registered and its hosted zone exists in AWS Route 53</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"17c5bbcd1ac4">
<p local-id=3D"a0d35d4d9988">The Hello World application code is available =
and ready to deploy</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c3dbbce364d8">
<p local-id=3D"c870c4d7734b">The local Windows machine has PowerShell and <=
code>nslookup</code> available for DNS validation</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1cd16eb632e6">
<p local-id=3D"c6eab606284f">DNS TTL of 300 seconds is acceptable for this =
PoC</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"af4daf66c688">
<h2 local-id=3D"cc83ef5c2238" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-3.Architecture=
andInfrastructure">3. Architecture and Infrastructure</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"44ca85d7a6a4" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-3.1Infrastruct=
ureOverview">3.1 Infrastructure Overview</h3>
<p local-id=3D"898c8d8d3c64">The solution uses Azure App Service as the Paa=
S hosting platform for the Hello World application. DNS is managed via AWS =
Route 53 with CNAME and TXT records pointing the custom domain to the Azure=
 App Service default domain. The application is accessible both via the def=
ault Azure URL and the custom domain.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">+------=
---------------------+
|   Local Windows Machine   |
|   Browser / PowerShell    |
+---------------------------+
           |
           | HTTPS request to app.karna.pushkar.cloud
           v
+---------------------------+
|   AWS Route 53            |
|   Hosted Zone:            |
|   karna.pushkar.cloud     |
|                           |
|   CNAME: app --&gt;          |
|   karna-app-service-      |
|   grf3c8due9efcdg9.       |
|   centralus-01.           |
|   azurewebsites.net       |
|                           |
|   TXT: asuid.app --&gt;      |
|   Domain Verification ID  |
+---------------------------+
           |
           | DNS resolves CNAME to Azure default domain
           v
+------------------------------------------+
|   Microsoft Azure                        |
|   Region: Central US                     |
|                                          |
|   App Service Plan: ASP-kmlrgmain        |
|   (P0v3: 1, Linux)                       |
