<p local-id=3D"e2aaeb84463b">Note: For this PoC implementation, a single en=
vironment is used. In a production setup, separate Dev, Staging, and Produc=
tion App Service slots would be configured.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"87714bf39cce" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-3.3Application=
ArchitectureandUserRequestFlow">3.3 Application Architecture and User Reque=
st Flow</h3>
<p local-id=3D"06eac0050301"><strong>Application Architecture:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">User Br=
owser
     |
     | https://app.karna.pushkar.cloud
     v
AWS Route 53 (DNS Resolution)
     |
     | CNAME: app.karna.pushkar.cloud
     |   --&gt; karna-app-service-grf3c8due9efcdg9.centralus-01.azurewebsit=
es.net
     v
Azure Front-end Load Balancer (Central US)
     |
     v
Azure App Service Plan (P0v3 Linux)
     |
     v
Web App: karna-app-service (Python 3.14)
     |
     v
Application Response: "Hello World from Azure!"</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"0c8ce22c7813"><strong>Secured User Request Flow:</strong></p=
>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Step 1:=
 User navigates to https://app.karna.pushkar.cloud
Step 2: Browser queries DNS (AWS Route 53)
Step 3: Route 53 returns CNAME value:
        karna-app-service-grf3c8due9efcdg9.centralus-01.azurewebsites.net
Step 4: Browser resolves Azure domain to IP (40.122.36.65)
Step 5: HTTPS request reaches Azure App Service
Step 6: App Service serves: "Hello World from Azure!"
Step 7: Response displayed in browser

DNS Verification Flow (Domain Ownership):
Step 1: Azure provides verification ID (TXT record value)
Step 2: TXT record created in Route 53:
        asuid.app.karna.pushkar.cloud --&gt;
        "4F56E2DED9F8828991B87FE61AFAE9B29DBDA673AC84C957EED4876CD6DC66E9"
Step 3: Azure validates TXT record to confirm domain ownership
Step 4: Custom domain mapping approved and activated</pre>
</div>
</div>
