<hr local-id=3D"b6fa980b822c">
<h2 local-id=3D"dd5da6cff5be" id=3D"Task21-TechnicalDocument-AppendixA:SOAR=
ecord=E2=80=94FullFieldDocumentation">Appendix A: SOA Record =E2=80=94 Full=
 Field Documentation</h2>
<p local-id=3D"0cfd32d7c76f">The SOA (Start of Authority) record is the fir=
st record in any DNS zone. It defines authoritative information about the z=
one and controls how DNS data is propagated across servers.</p>
<p local-id=3D"cf73453632b7"><strong>SOA Record for </strong><code>karna.pu=
shkar.cloud</code><strong> zone:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"2=
8a25231-ebf5-4991-bb00-4587254e7e39" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"241620a004f4">
<th data-local-id=3D"2e40b2f80727" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"cd1de4408021">Order</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"778c9cebf70e" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"f9866c28c266">Field Name</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"cdc75c715efd" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ef9e6260ae24">Unit</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"1dabd975441a" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"8e7288ef81c4">Purpose</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"e5be787e1c40" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"dc5759f4706f">Simple Explanation</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"6d33cb2cf202">
<td data-local-id=3D"9ae33bc62d4f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4407431f6579">1</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5d8eba27f6c2" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"017dee6670d8">MNAME</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"80c76f17c24d" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b8ae271c1ba0">Hostname</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"9a2ab35ac35c" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c990bd8ec9d8">Primary DNS Server</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4d5d5914f4be" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"055db3773b9e">The name of the main DNS server that holds the=
 original copy of the zone file. All DNS changes are made here first.</p></=
td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"a22ea66fa47c">
<td data-local-id=3D"f76facbe5037" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c2a2fab09cfa">2</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b3d66ae20c52" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"be6b6bbd1296">RNAME</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6dabe0ef7143" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"97a5a9587a5d">Email</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8295bebc3af6" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"41d5048bb7e1">Admin Contact</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f07a37535516" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5e37228acb93">The email address of the person responsible fo=
r managing the DNS zone. The <code>@</code> symbol is replaced with a dot (=
e.g., <code>admin.karna.pushkar.cloud</code> means <code>admin@karna.pushka=
r.cloud</code>).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"35506b947edd">
<td data-local-id=3D"3d9402b14794" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4f8fafc6e99b">3</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f6cd0ee9b6f5" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fd48ba578ed8">SERIAL</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5283d27b7d69" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"edadeda2df51">Number</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"08964eb5621c" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"abbadbc12167">Version Control</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e4fcf2229906" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"15cd62e56988">A number that increases every time the DNS zon=
e is updated. Secondary DNS servers compare their serial number to the prim=
ary to know if they need to sync.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"7263617658eb">
<td data-local-id=3D"e5a48b6af2ce" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bdb3134043c6">4</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"340162fbc3b1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"899b8c0d2fb6">REFRESH</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1fc53d9a59a5" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"16c025670ae1">Seconds</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"adfdec3be2d1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bb32916b6df1">Sync Interval</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"72d40db296b7" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7774c3ee7aae">How often (in seconds) secondary DNS servers c=
heck the primary server to see if the zone data has changed and needs to be=
 refreshed.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"49a9f0ad98f0">
<td data-local-id=3D"877ff18ccc9f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1baa833d2610">5</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"85c0156e5180" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0db89582ed49">RETRY</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8c86fec90678" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7637fae93465">Seconds</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e3374fc6db02" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4a19c758f6be">Wait time after sync failure</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c1ad17ede750" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d05381d06105">If a secondary server fails to contact the pri=
mary during a refresh, this value defines how long it waits before trying a=
gain.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"82bf7032a655">
<td data-local-id=3D"931e01d61b1e" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"60fa2f19ccc9">6</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6c88a773495b" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9e69b06cbe93">EXPIRE</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c086cff7339d" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f1f1499dc3c8">Seconds</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"53c83047641e" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cb99184236bc">When to stop serving old data</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4e3b71d4165f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5bc2d4d5bf70">If a secondary server cannot reach the primary=
 for this amount of time, it stops serving DNS responses for that zone enti=
rely, as the data may be too outdated to be reliable.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ba0c82d55fcf">
<td data-local-id=3D"086c822a142f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"915ae612e625">7</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"2d82aafe0d00" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"50e9f8195f3e">MIN TTL</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"fbd1037b7b8f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8d67017512c6">Seconds</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3ee2086cb156" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"539670b14a07">How long to cache "Not Found"</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3f8d1f17f763" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ae702c8afa9d">The minimum time (in seconds) that a negative =
response (i.e., "this domain does not exist") should be cached by resolvers=
. This prevents repeated lookups for non-existent domains.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"7ebdd605a97a"><strong>For AWS Route 53 hosted zones, typical=
 SOA values are:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"5d8499070256">
<li local-id=3D"8a8e941016ef">
<p local-id=3D"180d765fce65">MNAME: <code>ns-XXXX.awsdns-XX.com</code> (Rou=
te 53 primary nameserver)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"49b1708c7b4d">
<p local-id=3D"01f084f81203">RNAME: <code>awsdns-hostmaster.amazon.com</cod=
e></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"de8559da2010">
<p local-id=3D"f633d4d6d771">SERIAL: Auto-incremented by Route 53 on every =
change</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a6d089f800fd">
<p local-id=3D"0acb3543ea9d">REFRESH: 7200 seconds (2 hours)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2409fe5b8186">
<p local-id=3D"5d8003406719">RETRY: 900 seconds (15 minutes)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c7768e4e3a51">
<p local-id=3D"ca3d65a91810">EXPIRE: 1209600 seconds (14 days)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d2d1c5f41be7">
<p local-id=3D"e01296cb19b7">MIN TTL: 86400 seconds (1 day)</p></li>
</ul>
